HEADWORD: Cuspidated
<hw>Cus"pi*da`ted</hw> <pr>(-d?`t?d)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>cuspidatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>cuspidare</ets> to make
pointed, fr. <ets>cuspis</ets>. See <er>Cusp</er>.]</ety> <def>Having a
sharp end, like the point of a spear; terminating in a hard point;
<as>as, a <ex>cuspidate</ex> leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

